<LegalLayout
  title="Data Security"
  description="How Pacific Ocean Tech protects your data, intellectual property, and infrastructure."
  slug="security"
>
  <h1>Data Security</h1>
  <p>Pacific Ocean Tech takes the security of your data and intellectual property seriously. This page outlines the measures we have in place to protect our clients.</p>

  <h2>Infrastructure security</h2>
  <p>All engineering operations are conducted on secure, monitored networks. We enforce encrypted connections (TLS 1.2+), endpoint protection, and centralized access management across all environments.</p>

  <h2>Access controls</h2>
  <p>We implement role-based access controls, multi-factor authentication, and least-privilege principles. Access to client systems is granted only to assigned team members and revoked immediately upon disengagement.</p>

  <h2>Intellectual property protection</h2>
  <p>Every professional signs strict non-disclosure agreements and IP assignment contracts before engagement. Your code, data, and proprietary information remain 100% yours.</p>

  <h2>Compliance</h2>
  <p>Our facilities maintain ISO-aligned security practices. We conduct regular security audits and vulnerability assessments to ensure ongoing compliance with industry standards.</p>

  <h2>Incident response</h2>
  <p>We maintain a documented incident response plan. In the event of a security incident, affected clients are notified within 24 hours with a full remediation timeline.</p>

  <h2>Questions</h2>
  <p>For security inquiries, contact <a href="mailto:security@pacificoceantech.com">security@pacificoceantech.com</a>.</p>
</LegalLayout>
